{"key":"processedPost-8522849","value":{"id":8522849,"first":8522728,"last":8523334,"when":1213455650,"utime":"06/14/08 06:00 PM","content":"Guys, cased rye makes an excellent fruiting substrate.&nbsp; In fact, it's probably second only to brf cakes in BE.&nbsp; Tapered, small mouth jars are also perfect for rye berries.&nbsp; Bang them against a fully inflated tire or tree trunk, phone book, etc., to break the grains up, and then they can be poured out of the jar like sand.<br /><br />Rye by definition isn't a bulk substrate.&nbsp; It can be cased and fruited directly with excellent performance, or it can be used as spawn to a bulk substrate such as manure, coir, straw, etc.<br />RR","title":"Re: rye = bad substrate"}}